entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah what is the best thing about being a parent

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: just seeing them grow and and experience new things and learn about life and the world it is just it is really really cool

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are some ways that you are different as a parent than your parents

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: completely different completely different i and i am not a perfect parent but i love my son i take care of him he is the first priority in my life and they were not like that at all

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about your relationship with your family

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well my parents are dead i did not speak to my dad at all before he died i have a sister and a brother that actually i do not know where they are i do not speak to them either

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay do you consider yourself more shy or outgoing

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: probably more shy because i consider myself more reserved

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: sometimes when i am feeling tense i turn on the fish tank screensaver hey i know it is not hawaii but it is the best i have got what do you do to relax

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i like to listen to music

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i found out he was cheating on me and i kicked him out and he told me yesterday that he is continuing to date her

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that sounds really hard

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how did you feel in that moment

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: really angry and just really hurt

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah i am sorry tell me about a situation that you wish you had handled differently

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i wish that i had talked to my dad before he died i wish that i would settled our differences before he had died

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about the hardest decision you have ever had to make

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: the hardest decision i have ever had to make was actually ending my marriage

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it is just because of everything that i am going through with my soon to be ex husband yeah there is

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how do you cope with them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i just keep it inside i mean there is nothing else to really do except i mean it is what it is so i have to deal with it

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how long ago were you diagnosed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: ten years ago after my son was born

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what got you to seek help

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: or nine years ago i felt like i could not cope with life i was so down i could not i felt like i could not do anything

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: are they triggered by something

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you still go to therapy now

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i do not go to therapy i go to medication management but i do not i do not do talk therapy

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: is going to a therapist helping you

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i have gone to therapists and no they do not help

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well some just sit and stare at you and do not say anything you know if i wanted to talk to myself i would others give advice that i think is just it just not not good and not on point

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah tell me about the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it was probably this morning i was playing with my son
